text: is a Japanese football player. She played for the Japan national team. ==Biography== Seike was born in Tokyo Metropolis on August 8, 1996. In 2014, she joined Nadeshiko League club Urawa Reds from their youth team. In 2015, she was selected Best Young Player Award.Nadeshiko League In December 2019, Seike was selected by the Japan national team for the EAFF E-1 Championship. At this tournament, she debuted and scored a goal against Chinese Taipei on December 11. ==Statistics== List of match in 2019 at Japan Football Association Japan national team Year Apps Goals 2019 2 1 Total 2 1 ==References== ==Other websites== * *Japan Football Association Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Footballers from Tokyo Prefecture Category:Japan women's international footballers Category:Nadeshiko League players Category:Urawa Red Diamonds Ladies players
